        <h3>How to use this repository</h3>
        
        To use the packages in this repository, add the following lines to
        
        <tt>/etc/apt/sources.list</tt>
        <pre>
	deb http://linux.pythonxy.com/ubuntu <i>release</i> universe
        deb-src http://linux.pythonxy.com/ubuntu <i>release</i> universe
	</pre>
        Replace <i>release</i> with one of the releases listed below. 
	A list of available components can be found on the release
        pages linked below.
        <pre></pre>
        Next, get my gpg key and add it to the apt-key list:
	<pre>
	wget http://linux.pythonxy.com/ubuntu/F213500F.gpg -O- | sudo apt-key add - 
	</pre>
	Don't forget to update apt list:
	<pre>
	sudo apt-get update <i> or </i> sudo aptitude update
	</pre>
	<h3>Additional repositories</h3>
	For ITK related packages, in <i>pythonxy-applications</i>, add the source list below:
        <pre>
	deb http://apt.paulnovo.org/ubuntu <i>release</i> main
	deb-src http://apt.paulnovo.org/ubuntu  <i>release</i> main</pre>
	And Key :
 	<pre>
	wget http://apt.paulnovo.org/549EC7E2.key -O- | sudo apt-key add - </pre>
	<h3>Releases</h3>
         Ubuntu releases are supported for 18 months. Ubuntu LTS (Long Term Support) releases are supported for 3 years on the desktop, and 5 years on the server.
        <dl> 
          <dt><a href="dists/hardy">hardy</a></dt>
          <dd class="half">Ubuntu 8.04 LTS - the current long term support version, released in April 2008, codenamed Hardy Heron.</dd>
          <dt><a href="dists/intrepid">intrepid</a></dt>
          <dd class="half">Ubuntu 8.10 - the current version, were released in October 30, 2008, codenamed Intrepid Ibex (le bouquetin intrepide).This version will be supported until April 2010, and will be followed by Ubuntu 9.04.
</dd>
          <dt><a href="dists/jaunty">jaunty</a></dt>
          <dd class="half">Ubuntu 9.04 has been released on april 23 2009, and is codenamed Jaunty Jackalope. It will be supported until October 2010 </dd>
        </dl>
